util

Class Debug

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.Debug

  • public class Debug
extends Object
    Debug provides a simple method to output debug statements that will not be shown in the final user product.

    All standard console output messages should be printed through Debug.

    By setting debugLevel during Debug construction, you decide which messages get displayed. Default debugLevel is Globals.DEBUG_LEVEL.

    Debug levels 

     0 - ALWAYS - file i/o errors, login information
 1 - HIGH -  i/o errors
 2 - MEDIUM - socket i/o
 3 - LOW - function calls
    A debug message will only be displayed if its debug level is less than or equal to Debug.debugLevel.

    In the case of a FilterHandler or AlgorithmHandler, you may want more specific information about which Filter or Algorithm this handler applies to. In such a case, use the Debug.x(int level,String name,String output) methods.

    Author:
    Kyle
